The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      The City Diary
                Three snatchers, including a six-year-old girl and her mother, were arrested from the City Centre food court on Saturday evening. Babulal Bothra, his sister-in-law Babita Jain and the child were intercepted by security guards after the girl picked up a customers bag and ran away. The customer raised an alarm. Debit cards, credit cards and Rs 5,000 were in the bag. Cops said Babulal, a Howrah resident, used the kid to steal valuables from malls, fairs and eateries. The three were produced in the Salt Lake additional chief judicial magistrates court on Sunday. Babulal was remanded in judicial custody for seven days. Babita and the child were released on bail.     A gold jewellery trader in his early 50s was assaulted by four youths who tried to snatch his bag at Domjur on Saturday night. Swapan Dey was returning from his Bowbazar workshop to his Domjur home when the youths, who came on two motorcycles, attacked him. Dey sustained injuries on his head, face and hands. Bhaskar Karati, one of the youths, was caught by residents of the area.     Umesh Das and Meera Das were arrested in a slum on Umesh Chandra Das Road in Phoolbagan on Saturday night for allegedly abetting the suicide of Umeshs wife 27-year-old Sampa Das. Police said Sampa was found hanging from the ceiling fan of her room on Saturday morning. In the evening, Sampas parents lodged a police complaint alleging that she was regularly tortured by Umesh and his former wife Meera, who lived in the slum.     Three persons were arrested at a soft drink distribution centre in Muchipara on Sunday following a complaint by the authorities of a multinational company that some people in connivance with the distributors of a rival had stolen over 50 empty bottles to fill them with spurious drinks to malign the company.    A 35-year-old drug pedlar was arrested on Strand Bank Road on Saturday. Around 40 grams of heroin was seized from Saraswati Parshi. Police said Parshi was involved in the racket for the past few years.    State health minister Surjya Kanta Mishra inaugurated a neurogenetic unit at Bangur Institute of Neurosciences on Saturday.     A Tata Sumo (WB-02S-5003) was stolen from Congress Exhibition Road in Park Circus on Saturday. Police said the car was parked in front of 7C Congress Exhibition Road. Owner Deepak Kumar Walia lodged a police complaint.    Employees of Calcutta Metropolitan Water and Sanitation Authority on Sunday threatened to stop water supply to the Calcutta Municipal Corporation if it did not clear its dues immediately. The agency supplies 75 million gallons of water every day to the civic body from its Garden Reach Water Treatment Plant. The monthly bill is Rs 3.5 crore but the CMC pays only Rs 1 crore.          
